# ⭐ FOURTH: What you’re not seeing yet (but you’re close)

You’re missing **one architectural layer**:

## A Node Type Registry

Right now, your engine does this:

```js
if (node.type === "timer") { ... }
if (node.type === "portal") { ... }
if (node.type === "wordPuzzle") { ... }
if (node.type === "gem") { ... }
```

This works, but it **does not scale**.

When you hit 10–15 node types, this becomes:

- Hard to maintain  
- Hard to test  
- Hard to extend  
- Hard to debug  
- Easy to break  

A commercial-grade engine uses:

```js
const NODE_RENDERERS = {
  story: renderStory,
  puzzle: renderPuzzle,
  wordPuzzle: renderWordPuzzle,
  portal: renderPortal,
  timer: renderTimer,
  gem: renderGem,
  end: renderEnd
};
```

Then:

```js
const renderer = NODE_RENDERERS[node.type] || renderDefault;
renderer(node);
```

This gives you:

- Infinite scalability  
- Zero drift  
- Zero duplication  
- Perfect isolation  
- Perfect testability  
- Perfect extensibility  

This is the missing piece.

